  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern</discussion>
  <discussion>Subspecies bettinae can form clumps to 4 dm in diameter.  It is known from near the coast west of San Luis Obispo and west of the range of subsp. murina; it is considered fairly endangered (California Native Plant Society, http://cnps.web.aplus.net/cgi-bin/inv/inventory.cgi).  R. F. Hoover (1965, 1970) listed as Dudleya parva what seems to be a smaller form of this subspecies, local near San Bernardo Creek and the mouth of Chorro Creek.</discussion>
